'''Donald Runnicles''' (born ,  in , ) is a  . He attended the . He began his operatic career as a singers' coach in Mannheim, Germany. He became ''Generalmusikdirektor'' of the city of ,  in 1989.
Runnicles has been  and Principal Conductor of the  since 1992.  His prior contract renewal was in November 2004.<ref>{{cite news | author=Ben Mattison | title=San Francisco Opera Music Director Donald Runnicles Extends His Tenure | url=http://www.playbillarts.com/news/article/770.html | work=Playbill Arts | date=2004-11-16 | accessdate=2007-12-21}}</ref>  In September 2006, he and the company mutually agreed that he would relinquish his post after the 2008-2009 season, but would continue to work with the company as a guest conductor.<ref>{{cite news | author=Matthew Westphal | title=Donald Runnicles's Contract at San Francisco Opera Will Not Be Renewed | url=http://www.playbillarts.com/news/article/5236.html | work=Playbill Arts | date=2006-09-18 | accessdate=2007-12-21}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news | author=Joshua Kosman | title=Runnicles won't renew contract with S.F. Opera | url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2006/09/16/DDGJOL63271.DTL | work=San Francisco Chronicle | date=2006-09-16 | accessdate=2007-10-03}}</ref>
Runnicles has served as Prinicipal Guest Conductor of the  since September 2001, and his current contract there runs through 2009.<ref>{{cite news | author=Ben Mattison | title=Atlanta Symphony Extends Contracts of Spano and Runnicles | url=http://www.playbillarts.com/news/article/2909.html | work=Playbill Arts | date=2005-09-21 | accessdate=2007-12-23}}</ref>  In March 2008, the orchestra and Runnicles announced the extension of his contract as principal guest conductor through the 2010-2011 season, after which he is scheduled to relinquish the title.<ref>{{cite news | title=Musical director, principal guest conductor of Atlanta Symphony Orchestra renew contracts
 | url=http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2008/03/18/arts/NA-A-E-MUS-US-Atlanta-Symphony.php | work=The Associated Press | date=2008-03-18 | accessdate=2008-03-19}}</ref>  From 2001 to 2007, he was also Principal Conductor of the .  He became Music Director of the  in September 2005, having been appointed that August.<ref>{{cite news | author=Emily Quinn | title=Donald Runnicles Named Next Music Director of Grand Teton Music Festival | url=http://www.playbillarts.com/news/article/2748.html | work=Playbill Arts | date=2005-08-29 | accessdate=2007-12-23}}</ref>  His current Grand Teton contract is through 2011.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2007/10/02/DD7VSHQG6.DTL&feed=rss.classical | title=Opera's Runnicles to lead BBC Scottish Symphony Orchestra | publisher=''San Francisco Chronicle'' | author=Joshua Kosman | date=2007-10-02 | accessdate=2007-11-20}}</ref>
In October 2007, the  announced that Runnicles will become their next Chief Conductor in September 2009, for an initial contract of 3 years.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://thescotsman.scotsman.com/entertainment.cfm?id=1572202007 | title=Conductor back after 18 years to lead BBC Scottish Symphony Orchestra | publisher=''The Scotsman'' | author=Tim Cornwell | date=2007-10-02 | accessdate=2007-10-03}}</ref>  Later the same month, the  announced the appointment of Runnicles as their next ''Generalmusikdirektor'', effective August 2009, for an initial contract of 5 years.<ref>{{cite news | author=Matthew Westphal | title=In Sudden Appointment, Donald Runnicles Named Next Music Director of Deutsche Oper Berlin | url=http://www.playbillarts.com/news/article/7298.html | work=Playbill Arts | date=2007-10-31 | accessdate=2007-11-01}}</ref>
Runnicles and his wife have three daughters, Alexandra, Ashley and Tamara.<ref>{{cite news | author=Frederik Hanssen | title=Der neue Maestro | url=http://www.tagesspiegel.de/kultur/Musik-Deutsche-Oper;art971,2411249 | work=Der Tagesspiegel | date=2007-11-01 | accessdate=2007-11-03}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news | author=Michael Tumelty | title=Now heâ€™s conducting electricity | url=http://www.theherald.co.uk/search/display.var.1734015.0.now_hes_conducting_electricity.php | work=The Herald | date=2007-10-04 | accessdate=2007-11-20}}</ref>